\SE[2]Um... about this quest? \SE[3]Inspecting the frontier
village...? What am I supposed to do?

\SE[2]The destination is the frontier village called Hajikko
Village. \SE[3]This place doesn't belong to Yurisine, but we
have a friendly treaty, so we maintain regular contact.

\SE[2]It seems that this has been cut off for the past three
months. \SE[38]There is a direct road connection, but it
seems that it cannot be used right now due to a landslide.

\SE[2]While we confirm the situation in Hajikko Village...
\!\SE[0]If necessary, we can incorporate the opinions of the
locals and report to the important people in Yurisine. That
should be the end, I suppose.

\SE[3]Hmmm...? \SE[8]It's kind of complicated... I wonder if
I can do it...

\SE\SM[nod]\SE[15]Don't worry. I'll take care of all the
reports, and Laura can gradually get used to it.
\SM[nod]\SE[15]It's your first quest. Let's do our best
together.

We're here on a hiking trip. Enjoying the scenery while
beating up monsters... Taking a nice break with our
partner... It's the best, isn't it?

I used too much magic and ran out of MP.... \! If you're
tired too, make sure to take a proper rest, okay?

The monsters are happily gazing at the waterfall....
\!...Shall we begin the battle?\!
There's a strong-looking monster.... Will you fight it?

It's a monument for defeating unique monsters.... \! Will
you have a rematch with the selfish fairy? \!

Yaa, otsukare. So, have you started getting used to
adventuring?

Huh, huh? You're doing well, huh? It's not like I'd be
disappointed if you cleared it with ease, you know? It's
within the expected range, right???

That's commendable...! Well, but I think approaching things
with that kind of attitude will lead to the best results...

Don't worry... You can do it! I believe in you...!! Show me
your spirit! Everything can be solved with spirit and
muscles!!

Ah, it looks tough...? If that's the case, why don't you try
changing the difficulty level?

By changing the difficulty level from the Options menu, you
can alter the balance of battles. If you're not good at or
unfamiliar with RPGs, please feel free to use it.

If it's too Sweet, it might be too easy... Maybe Easy would
be just the right balance... I wonder...?

By the way, I haven't told you yet... You can speed up
conversation events and battles by holding down the 'Ctrl'
key or 'Alt' key.

I think it's convenient when you're in a hurry. It's almost
like a skip speed, so just be careful not to miss anything
important.
